WEBVTT

1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,000
TED：吸引力的科学
The science of attraction

2
00:00:07,290 --> 00:00:10,117
We like to think of romantic feelings as spontaneous
我们总认为恋爱的感觉是不可预测

3
00:00:10,117 --> 00:00:13,283
and indescribable things that come from the heart.
无法形容的心理感受

4
00:00:13,283 --> 00:00:15,571
But it's actually your brain running a complex
但其实那是你的脑袋在数秒之间

5
00:00:15,571 --> 00:00:18,770
series of calculations within a matter of seconds
处理一连串复杂的计算

6
00:00:18,770 --> 00:00:21,757
that's responsible for determining attraction.
最后决定了什么对你有吸引力

7
00:00:21,757 --> 00:00:23,883
Doesn't sound quite as poetic, does it?
听起来一点也不浪漫，对吧？

8
00:00:23,883 --> 00:00:26,393
But just because the calculations are happening in your brain
但就算你脑袋里转着计算公式

9
00:00:26,393 --> 00:00:30,158
doesn't mean those warm, fuzzy feelings are all in your head.
不代表那个温热柔软的感觉
都只是你的幻觉

10
00:00:30,158 --> 00:00:32,675
In fact, all five of your senses play a role,
事实上，你的五个感官也各出了一份力

11
00:00:32,675 --> 00:00:36,805
each able to vote for, or veto, a budding attraction.
投票通过或否决刚滋长的爱苗

12
00:00:36,805 --> 00:00:39,549
The eyes are the first components in attraction.
眼睛是参与吸引力决策
的第一个成员

13
00:00:39,549 --> 00:00:41,237
Many visual beauty standards vary
视觉审美标准在各文化、时代之间皆相异

14
00:00:41,237 --> 00:00:43,116
between cultures and eras,
视觉审美标准在
各文化、时代之间皆相异

15
00:00:43,116 --> 00:00:45,665
and signs of youth, fertility and good health,
年轻、生育力
与健康的征象也都不同

16
00:00:45,665 --> 00:00:47,482
such as long lustrous hair,
例如有光泽的长长秀发

17
00:00:47,482 --> 00:00:49,851
or smooth, scar-free skin,
或光滑无痕的肌肤

18
00:00:49,851 --> 00:00:51,312
are almost always in demand
几乎总是需求不断

19
00:00:51,312 --> 00:00:54,384
because they're associated with reproductive fitness.
因为这些和繁衍后代的能力有关

20
00:00:54,384 --> 00:00:56,331
And when the eyes spot something they like,
而当眼睛看见喜欢的事物时

21
00:00:56,331 --> 00:00:58,598
our instinct is to move closer
我们的本能便是靠上前

22
00:00:58,598 --> 00:01:00,943
so the other senses can investigate.
好让其他的感官也能够侦察

23
00:01:00,943 --> 00:01:02,819
The nose's contribution to romance
鼻子对于爱情的贡献

24
00:01:02,819 --> 00:01:05,612
is more than noticing perfume or cologne.
不只是注意到香水或古龙水而已

25
00:01:05,612 --> 00:01:08,237
It's able to pick up on natural chemical signals
鼻子也接收自然化学物质的信号

26
00:01:08,237 --> 00:01:09,803
known as pheromones.
这类物质称作费洛蒙

27
00:01:09,803 --> 00:01:11,659
These not only convey important
费洛蒙不只传达关于其来源的

28
00:01:11,659 --> 00:01:14,553
physical or genetic information about their source
生理或基因的重要信息

29
00:01:14,553 --> 00:01:16,764
but are able to activate a physiological
也能引发信号接受者

30
00:01:16,764 --> 00:01:20,054
or behavioral response in the recipient.
在生理上或行为上的回应

31
00:01:20,054 --> 00:01:24,196
In one study, a group of women at different points in their ovulation cycles
某研究曾让一群
在月经周期不同阶段的女人

32
00:01:24,196 --> 00:01:26,525
wore the same t-shirts for three nights.
穿着同一件衣服三晚

33
00:01:26,525 --> 00:01:29,005
After male volunteers were randomly assigned
再随机指定男性自愿者

34
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:31,266
to smell either one of the worn shirts,
闻那些被穿过的衣服

35
00:01:31,266 --> 00:01:32,997
or a new unworn one,
或是没人穿过的新衣服之后

36
00:01:32,997 --> 00:01:36,765
saliva samples showed an increase in testosterone
唾液采样显示
闻排卵期女性穿过衣物的男性

37
00:01:36,765 --> 00:01:40,531
in those who had smelled a shirt worn by an ovulating woman.
身上睪固酮量增加了

38
00:01:40,531 --> 00:01:42,199
Such a testosterone boost
这样的睪固酮激增

39
00:01:42,199 --> 00:01:44,768
may give a man the nudge to persue a woman
就可能驱使男人去追求一位

40
00:01:44,768 --> 00:01:47,028
he might not have otherwise noticed.
他原来也许不会注意到的女人

41
00:01:47,028 --> 00:01:49,183
A woman's nose is particularly attuned
女人的鼻子则对

42
00:01:49,183 --> 00:01:51,303
to MHC molecules,
主要组织兼容性复合体 (MHC) 分子特别敏锐

43
00:01:51,303 --> 00:01:53,361
which are used to fight disease.
这是用来抗病的分子

44
00:01:53,361 --> 00:01:55,617
In this case, opposites attract.
在这种情形下，异性就会相吸

45
00:01:55,617 --> 00:01:58,148
When a study asked women to smell t-shirts
当实验要求女人闻

46
00:01:58,148 --> 00:02:00,056
that had been worn by different men,
不同男人穿过的 T 恤时

47
00:02:00,056 --> 00:02:02,193
they preferred the odors of those whose
她们偏好与自己

48
00:02:02,193 --> 00:02:05,176
MHC molecules differed from theirs.
不同 MHC 分子的气味

49
00:02:05,176 --> 00:02:06,402
This makes sense.
这不无道理

50
00:02:06,402 --> 00:02:09,109
Genes that result in a greater variety of immunities
免疫能力多元的基因

51
00:02:09,109 --> 00:02:12,507
may give offspring a major survival advantage.
可能给后代重要的存活优势

52
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:15,235
Our ears also determine attraction.
我们的耳朵也能决定吸引力

53
00:02:15,235 --> 00:02:18,660
Men prefer females with high-pitched, breathy voices,
男人比较喜欢女人的声音频率高、气声多

54
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:20,828
and wide formant spacing,
共振峰间距宽

55
00:02:20,828 --> 00:02:22,864
correlated with smaller body size.
代表了较小的体形

56
00:02:22,864 --> 00:02:25,402
While women prefer low-pitched voices
而女人则偏爱低频的声音

57
00:02:25,402 --> 00:02:27,316
with a narrow formant spacing
共振峰间距窄

58
00:02:27,316 --> 00:02:29,565
that suggest a larger body size.
表示体形较大

59
00:02:29,565 --> 00:02:31,013
And not surprisingly,
以及，意料之中

60
00:02:31,013 --> 00:02:33,530
touch turns out to be crucial for romance.
触觉对爱情来说是很关键的

61
00:02:33,530 --> 00:02:34,921
In this experiment,
在这个研究中

62
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:37,220
not realizing the study had begun,
不知实验已开始的受试者

63
00:02:37,220 --> 00:02:40,998
participants were asked to briefly hold the coffee,
被要求暂时拿着一杯咖啡

64
00:02:40,998 --> 00:02:42,746
either hot or iced.
可能是冰的也可能是热的

65
00:02:42,746 --> 00:02:44,505
Later, the participants read a story
之后，受试者阅读一篇故事

66
00:02:44,505 --> 00:02:46,274
about a hypothetical person,
内容关于一个虚构的人物

67
00:02:46,274 --> 00:02:48,406
and were asked to rate their personality.
他们被要求评价这个人物的个性

68
00:02:48,406 --> 00:02:50,843
Those who had held the hot cup of coffee
拿着热咖啡的人

69
00:02:50,843 --> 00:02:53,738
perceived the person in the story as happier,
对故事人物认知为较开心

70
00:02:53,738 --> 00:02:57,556
more social, more generous and better-natured
也较愿意交际、大方，较温和的人

71
00:02:57,556 --> 00:03:00,270
than those who had held the cup of iced coffee,
比照拿冰咖啡的受试者的看法

72
00:03:00,270 --> 00:03:04,793
who rated the person as cold, stoic, and unaffectionate.
他们则认为这个人物冷漠、严谨、不热情

73
00:03:04,793 --> 00:03:06,583
If a potential mate has managed to pass
如果有某个可能的对象通过

74
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:09,378
all these tests, there's still one more:
这些检验，最后还有一项：

75
00:03:09,378 --> 00:03:11,979
the infamous first kiss,
恶名昭彰的初吻

76
00:03:11,979 --> 00:03:13,976
a rich and complex exchange
初吻交换丰富而复杂的

77
00:03:13,976 --> 00:03:16,508
of tactile and chemical cues,
触觉及化学信号

78
00:03:16,508 --> 00:03:18,210
such as the smell of one's breath,
像是呼吸的气味

79
00:03:18,210 --> 00:03:20,234
and the taste of their mouth.
及嘴巴的味道

80
00:03:20,234 --> 00:03:22,076
This magical moment is so critical
这个神奇的时刻非常关键

81
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:24,052
that a majority of men and women
以致于很多男人女人

82
00:03:24,052 --> 00:03:26,377
have reported losing their attraction to someone
都说过他们在糟糕的初吻经验后

83
00:03:26,377 --> 00:03:28,931
after a bad first kiss.
就对对方失去兴趣了

84
00:03:28,931 --> 00:03:30,318
Once attraction is confirmed,
一旦确认了吸引力

85
00:03:30,318 --> 00:03:31,696
your bloodstream is flooded
你的血液里便充满了

86
00:03:31,696 --> 00:03:33,229
with norepinephrine,
去甲肾上腺素

87
00:03:33,229 --> 00:03:35,541
activating your fight or flight system.
启动你的「打或逃」机制

88
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:37,163
Your heart beats faster,
你的心跳加速

89
00:03:37,163 --> 00:03:38,533
your pupils dilate,
瞳孔放大

90
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:41,647
and your body releases glucose for additional energy,
身体释放出葡萄糖
以产生额外的能量

91
00:03:41,647 --> 00:03:43,084
not because you're in danger
不是因为你有危险了

92
00:03:43,084 --> 00:03:44,608
but because your body is telling you
而是你的身体在告诉你

93
00:03:44,608 --> 00:03:46,308
that something important is happening.
有件大事正在发生

94
00:03:46,318 --> 00:03:47,828
To help you focus,
为了让你能专注

95
00:03:47,828 --> 00:03:50,330
norepinephrine creates a sort of tunnel vision,
去甲肾上腺素制造出隧道视觉的效果

96
00:03:50,330 --> 00:03:52,625
blocking out surrounding distractions,
遮蔽周遭让你分心的东西

97
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:55,047
possibly even warping your sense of time,
可能甚至涷结你的时间感

98
00:03:55,047 --> 00:03:57,338
and enhancing your memory.
而增强你的记忆力

99
00:03:57,338 --> 00:04:01,139
This might explain why people never forget their first kiss.
这也许能解释为何人们总忘不了初吻

100
00:04:01,139 --> 00:04:03,058
The idea of so much of our attraction
知道了我们的吸引力

101
00:04:03,058 --> 00:04:06,323
being influenced by chemicals and evolutionary biology
是如此受化学物质与生物演化的影响

102
00:04:06,323 --> 00:04:09,287
may seem cold and scientific rather than romantic,
可能令人感觉无情、过于理性，一点也不浪漫

103
00:04:09,287 --> 00:04:11,323
but the next time you see someone you like,
但下次你遇见喜欢的人时

104
00:04:11,323 --> 00:04:15,344
try to appreciate how your entire body is playing matchmaker
试着感谢你的整个身体如何替你作媒

105
00:04:15,344 --> 00:04:18,700
to decide if that beautiful stranger is right for you.
来决定这个美丽的陌生人适不适合你

